<refsect2 id="gimp-image-grid-get-spacing" role="function" condition="since:GIMP 2.4">
<title>gimp_image_grid_get_spacing ()</title>
<indexterm zone="gimp-image-grid-get-spacing" role="GIMP 2.4"><primary>gimp_image_grid_get_spacing</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="gboolean">gboolean</link>            gimp_image_grid_get_spacing         (<link linkend="gint32">gint32</link> image_ID,
                                                         <link linkend="gdouble">gdouble</link> *xspacing,
                                                         <link linkend="gdouble">gdouble</link> *yspacing);</programlisting>
<para>
Gets the spacing of an image's grid.
</para>
<para>
This procedure retrieves the horizontal and vertical spacing of an
image's grid. It takes the image as parameter.</para>
<para>

</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>image_ID</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> The image.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><parameter>xspacing</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> The image's grid horizontal spacing.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><parameter>yspacing</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> The image's grid vertical spacing.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&nbsp;:</term><listitem><simpara> TRUE on success.

</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist><para role="since">Since  GIMP 2.4
</para></refsect2>
